00:11:56,580 --> 00:11:57,940
If Xingchi fails,

289
00:11:58,240 --> 00:11:59,620
just calculate the losses

290
00:11:59,880 --> 00:12:01,360
and deduct them from my options.

291
00:12:06,750 --> 00:12:08,730
Let me tell you, whether a system is strong or not

292
00:12:08,760 --> 00:12:10,510
all comes down to the order rejection rate.

293
00:12:10,540 --> 00:12:11,550
Take Yuntu, for example.

294
00:12:11,570 --> 00:12:13,570
If the number of rejected orders gets too high in one day,

295
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:14,360
the system will automatically...

296
00:12:14,380 --> 00:12:15,250
Xingchi.

297
00:12:15,290 --> 00:12:16,190
That won't do.

298
00:12:16,690 --> 00:12:17,520
Take it.

299
00:12:19,940 --> 00:12:20,790
Wanghe.

300
00:12:22,050 --> 00:12:23,270
The boss agreed.

301
00:12:26,760 --> 00:12:27,830
I owe you big time.

302
00:12:27,830 --> 00:12:29,190
Alright, knock it off.

303
00:12:29,960 --> 00:12:30,920
Just work hard.

304
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:32,500
But don't put too much pressure on yourself.

305
00:12:32,530 --> 00:12:33,570
There will definitely

306
00:12:33,910 --> 00:12:35,840
be gossip in the company.

307
00:12:35,910 --> 00:12:37,560
Don't take it to heart.

308
00:12:37,890 --> 00:12:40,430
From now on, you need to use your actions

309
00:12:40,450 --> 00:12:42,040
to prove them wrong.

310
00:12:42,590 --> 00:12:43,420
Don't worry.

311
00:12:43,650 --> 00:12:44,940
They'll know they're dead wrong!

312
00:12:49,140 --> 00:12:50,080
Guys,

313
00:12:49,220 --> 00:12:53,540
[Food Delivery Training]

314
00:12:50,580 --> 00:12:52,090
from today on,

315
00:12:52,110 --> 00:12:54,250
we sink or swim together.

316
00:12:54,430 --> 00:12:55,300
I don't know

317
00:12:55,340 --> 00:12:56,760
how things are in other stations.

318
00:12:56,790 --> 00:12:58,830
But here, the most important thing

319
00:12:59,060 --> 00:12:59,580
is fairness.

320
00:12:59,610 --> 00:13:00,370
Great!

321
00:13:02,610 --> 00:13:03,640
Clap.

322
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:11,120
[Food Delivery Training]

323
00:13:06,150 --> 00:13:07,110
At our station, I will

324
00:13:07,110 --> 00:13:09,270
do my best to distribute orders fairly.

325
00:13:09,470 --> 00:13:11,270
I won't make you take orders from over three kilometers away.

326
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:14,070
When something unexpected happens,

327
00:13:14,070 --> 00:13:14,830
don't panic, stay calm,

328
00:13:14,830 --> 00:13:15,750
and call the station.

329
00:13:15,830 --> 00:13:16,860
I'll handle it.

330
00:13:16,950 --> 00:13:19,100
If there's a dispute with a customer,

331
00:13:19,120 --> 00:13:20,640
don't panic either.

332
00:13:20,750 --> 00:13:21,870
Calm down

333
00:13:21,890 --> 00:13:24,000
and handle it according to the customer manual.

334
00:13:24,080 --> 00:13:25,240
If you can't handle it,

335
00:13:25,390 --> 00:13:26,110
leave it to me.

336
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:27,900
I won't let anyone take the blame.

337
00:13:27,930 --> 00:13:31,160
Great!

338
00:13:31,790 --> 00:13:33,270
Alright.

339
00:13:33,730 --> 00:13:35,280
Don't get excited yet.

340
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:36,660
What if I'm fooling you all?

341
00:13:36,950 --> 00:13:37,870
Right?

342
00:13:37,930 --> 00:13:39,070
We're out here hustling

343
00:13:39,140 --> 00:13:41,320
just to make our next meal a bit better.

344
00:13:42,560 --> 00:13:44,190
Whether you're truly capable or not,

345
00:13:44,210 --> 00:13:45,790
we'll find out after you're put to the test.

346
00:13:45,810 --> 00:13:47,230
That's all I have to say.

347
00:13:47,490 --> 00:13:48,850
Let's get rich!

348
00:13:48,860 --> 00:13:56,230
[Bee Delivery]

349
00:13:49,070 --> 00:13:49,740
Roll out!

350
00:13:49,870 --> 00:13:50,870
Yes.

351
00:13:50,870 --> 00:13:51,710
Roll out!

352
00:13:51,750 --> 00:13:52,590
Stay safe.

353
00:13:52,830 --> 00:13:53,710
Everyone, stay safe.

354
00:13:54,470 --> 00:13:55,230
Let's go.

355
00:13:55,310 --> 00:13:56,190
Let's go.

356
00:13:56,590 --> 00:13:57,370
Wang Yuan.

357
00:13:59,170 --> 00:13:59,810
You

358
00:13:59,970 --> 00:14:01,370
are always the loudest one.

359
00:14:02,060 --> 00:14:03,200
Listen.

360
00:14:03,230 --> 00:14:05,550
I only have one request for you.

361
00:14:05,570 --> 00:14:06,820
Don't get into fights.

362
00:14:06,860 --> 00:14:07,910
Don't worry.

363
00:14:07,930 --> 00:14:09,390
I'll just argue and won't get physical.

364
00:14:09,420 --> 00:14:10,720
You can't argue either.

365
00:14:10,740 --> 00:14:12,380
Just listen to whatever the client says.

366
00:14:12,420 --> 00:14:14,130
If you can't resolve it, hand it over to me.

367
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:16,430
I'm off then.

368
00:14:16,460 --> 00:14:17,060
Be careful on the road.

369
00:14:17,090 --> 00:14:18,020
Stay safe.

370
00:14:18,050 --> 00:14:18,800
Rest assured.

371
00:14:22,920 --> 00:14:26,510
[Fenghua Express]

372
00:14:29,780 --> 00:14:30,580
You're back?

373
00:14:31,210 --> 00:14:32,240
Mr. Sun?

374
00:14:33,010 --> 00:14:34,110
What brings you here?

375
00:14:34,230 --> 00:14:35,250
I'm here to talk with you

376
00:14:35,330 --> 00:14:36,310
about something.

377
00:14:36,670 --> 00:14:37,520
What is it?

378
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:38,390
Fenghua.

379
00:14:39,430 --> 00:14:41,200
Lychees from Guangdong.

380
00:14:41,470 --> 00:14:42,980
The three of us can't finish them all.

381
00:14:43,630 --> 00:14:44,740
You two carry on.

382
00:14:49,390 --> 00:14:52,190
Are you collaborating with Mr. Xie?

383
00:14:52,860 --> 00:14:54,890
He's in food delivery. I'm in parcel delivery.

384
00:14:54,910 --> 00:14:56,160
We're more like competitors.

385
00:14:56,180 --> 00:14:57,480
How could we possibly collaborate?

386
00:15:01,660 --> 00:15:02,390
Oh, right.

387
00:15:02,420 --> 00:15:03,470
I heard that

388
00:15:03,510 --> 00:15:04,630
recently,

389
00:15:04,630 --> 00:15:05,950
a lot of your people have left.

390
00:15:06,230 --> 00:15:07,510
How are you holding up?

391
00:15:10,340 --> 00:15:11,230
Fine.

392
00:15:11,670 --> 00:15:14,110
I've been trying to hire new people.

393
00:15:14,620 --> 00:15:15,950
Food delivery is really popular lately.

394
00:15:15,970 --> 00:15:16,870
It pays well too.

395
00:15:16,900 --> 00:15:17,950
It's not easy.

396
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:19,750
If you're overwhelmed,

397
00:15:21,060 --> 00:15:22,630
you could consider giving that area

398
00:15:22,790 --> 00:15:23,670
to someone else.

399
00:15:25,890 --> 00:15:27,020
What do you mean?

400
00:15:28,170 --> 00:15:29,420
You want to cut in on my business?

401
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:31,310
Aren't you overloaded?

402
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:32,940
I'm trying

403
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:35,750
to share your burden.

404
00:15:36,260 --> 00:15:38,440
After all, we're colleagues.

405
00:15:38,470 --> 00:15:41,470
Is this your idea or headquarters'?

406
00:15:43,350 --> 00:15:44,270
I think

407
00:15:44,350 --> 00:15:45,990
we can come up with a plan together first

408
00:15:45,990 --> 00:15:47,590
before I report it to headquarters.

409
00:15:47,590 --> 00:15:48,380
No need for that.

410
00:15:49,560 --> 00:15:50,770
We're doing well here.

411
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:51,890
We don't need anyone's help.

412
00:15:51,990 --> 00:15:53,110
Don't be so stubborn.

413
00:15:56,240 --> 00:15:58,060
How many people did you have before?

414
00:15:58,150 --> 00:16:00,350
How many do you have now?

415
00:16:05,620 --> 00:16:07,350
If you can't complete

416
00:16:07,350 --> 00:16:08,490
the assigned tasks,

417
00:16:09,650 --> 00:16:11,570
everyone here will be doomed.

418
00:16:11,810 --> 00:16:13,880
Don't worry about that.

419
00:16:14,400 --> 00:16:15,870
I am shorthanded,

420
00:16:15,920 --> 00:16:17,520
but I can still get things done.

421
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:19,390
When I do feel overwhelmed,

422
00:16:19,620 --> 00:16:21,230
I'll ask headquarters for help.

423
00:16:22,380 --> 00:16:23,830
By then, it'd be too late.

424
00:16:24,980 --> 00:16:27,030
The market nowadays

425
00:16:27,420 --> 00:16:28,540
is so competitive.

426
00:16:33,700 --> 00:16:34,460
Mr. Sun.

427
00:16:35,630 --> 00:16:37,870
I've always respected you as a senior

428
00:16:37,910 --> 00:16:40,390
and listened when you had something to say.

429
00:16:40,630 --> 00:16:42,220
For me,

430
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:44,000
this is a matter of survival.

431
00:16:44,270 --> 00:16:45,350
If you won't help me,

432
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:47,640
at least don't stab me in the back.

433
00:16:50,350 --> 00:16:52,740
You're too stubborn.

434
00:16:54,590 --> 00:16:55,430
Xia.

435
00:16:55,460 --> 00:16:56,990
Don't be impulsive.

436
00:16:57,110 --> 00:16:58,450
Think it through.

437
00:16:58,680 --> 00:16:59,840
In this era,

438
00:16:59,870 --> 00:17:01,040
changes happen so fast.

439
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:02,920
If you miss an opportunity,

440
00:17:02,940 --> 00:17:04,170
it's lost for good.

441
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:06,160
Think about it carefully.

442
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:08,670
[Parcel Delivery Safety Management]

443
00:17:09,300 --> 00:17:15,910
[Parcel Delivery Safety Management]

444
00:17:16,270 --> 00:17:18,020
He came to cut in on your business, right?

445
00:17:20,670 --> 00:17:22,550
He thinks he has seniority

446
00:17:22,710 --> 00:17:24,060
and once snatched orders from me.

447
00:17:24,670 --> 00:17:25,839
Seeing I'm short-staffed now,

448
00:17:25,880 --> 00:17:27,060
he wants to take advantage of it again.

449
00:17:27,220 --> 00:17:28,550
But I won't give him that satisfaction.

450
00:17:29,640 --> 00:17:31,130
So you're just going to tough it out?

451
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:33,030
You won't ask for help

452
00:17:33,300 --> 00:17:34,660
even if you're overloaded?

453
00:17:36,830 --> 00:17:38,710
I'll find a way to recruit people.

454
00:17:39,240 --> 00:17:40,240
How?

455
00:17:41,190 --> 00:17:42,330
By stealing my men?

456
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:43,880
Are you able to do that?

457
00:17:50,670 --> 00:17:51,790
I'm not able to do that.

458
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:54,650
So what do you suggest I do?

459
00:17:55,090 --> 00:17:57,370
I've thought of every possible solution.

460
00:17:57,390 --> 00:17:59,350
But any able-bodied man

461
00:17:59,350 --> 00:18:00,700
works in food delivery now.

462
00:18:20,630 --> 00:18:22,240
You can hire temps.

463
00:18:22,380 --> 00:18:23,500
Let them sort the parcels

464
00:18:24,060 --> 00:18:26,390
so the couriers can have more time to deliver.

465
00:18:28,210 --> 00:18:29,970
Wouldn't that cost a lot?

466
00:18:30,420 --> 00:18:33,410
Hourly workers in Haidian don't work full days.

467
00:18:33,450 --> 00:18:35,490
Part-time shifts would be even cheaper.

468
00:18:40,930 --> 00:18:41,960
Is it easy to manage them?

469
00:18:42,220 --> 00:18:43,100
Spend some money

470
00:18:43,150 --> 00:18:45,630
and have Haikuo write you a part-time shift management software.

471
00:18:45,670 --> 00:18:46,790
It's simple and quick.

472
00:18:51,950 --> 00:18:52,710
Okay.

473
00:18:53,300 --> 00:18:54,230
I'll think about it.

474
00:18:55,820 --> 00:18:57,290
Take your time. No rush.

475
00:19:03,140 --> 00:19:03,930
Is it sweet?

476
00:19:05,160 --> 00:19:05,920
Yes.

477
00:19:08,550 --> 00:19:10,450
Finish them before they go bad.

478
00:19:10,770 --> 00:19:15,110
[Fenghua Express]

479
00:19:28,890 --> 00:19:30,020
Fenghua.

480
00:19:30,150 --> 00:19:31,270
You're back so late.

481
00:19:31,310 --> 00:19:32,230
Let me heat up some food for you.

482
00:19:32,230 --> 00:19:34,640
It's okay. I'm not hungry. I'll make another delivery.

483
00:19:36,010 --> 00:19:38,470
Before food delivery was a thing,

484
00:19:38,470 --> 00:19:40,150
it was so easy to hire people.

485
00:19:40,150 --> 00:19:43,110
Just put up a sign, and people would come in droves.

486
00:19:43,550 --> 00:19:45,540
Every industry has its own challenges.

487
00:19:46,680 --> 00:19:49,080
Remember those first few years when we had to fight

488
00:19:49,100 --> 00:19:51,160
to keep our territory?

489
00:19:51,990 --> 00:19:53,700
I'll never forget that!

490
00:19:53,790 --> 00:19:55,490
You were a young girl

491
00:19:55,520 --> 00:19:57,740
but led dozens of people to argue with them.

492
00:19:58,230 --> 00:19:59,670
They hit your head with a shovel.

493
00:19:59,710 --> 00:20:01,880
Your scalp was turned inside out.

494
00:20:01,950 --> 00:20:02,910
Luckily, it didn't leave a scar on your face.

495
00:20:02,950 --> 00:20:05,050
I was scared to death at the time.

496
00:20:05,860 --> 00:20:07,150
Later,

497
00:20:07,550 --> 00:20:09,120
when you got stitches,

498
00:20:09,140 --> 00:20:10,330
you were actually smiling.

499
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:15,890
As the leader, I couldn't cry.

500
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:18,090
If I had cried, everyone else would've panicked.

501
00:20:19,620 --> 00:20:22,000
We're lucky to have had you all these years.

502
00:20:22,060 --> 00:20:23,960
You're the backbone for everyone.

503
00:20:23,990 --> 00:20:25,590
Only you can keep us together.

504
00:20:27,060 --> 00:20:29,100
Don't worry. Even if this station

505
00:20:29,140 --> 00:20:30,640
were to disband,

506
00:20:31,100 --> 00:20:33,880
I'd definitely be the last one to leave.

507
00:20:38,780 --> 00:20:39,750
Oh, by the way, Auntie,

508
00:20:39,790 --> 00:20:42,350
do you know any domestic workers?

509
00:20:43,840 --> 00:20:45,020
Plenty.

510
00:20:46,790 --> 00:20:48,950
Are you thinking about hiring hourly workers?

511
00:20:50,860 --> 00:20:52,310
Just tell me your requirements.

512
00:20:52,310 --> 00:20:53,570
I can introduce a lot of people to you.

513
00:20:53,610 --> 00:20:54,680
Also,

514
00:20:55,540 --> 00:20:57,290
would you consider someone not so young?

515
00:20:57,310 --> 00:20:58,300
Sure.

516
00:20:58,350 --> 00:21:01,540
Anyone who's diligent will do. The more, the better.

517
00:21:01,860 --> 00:21:04,150
Okay, I'll go call them now.

518
00:21:04,150 --> 00:21:05,510
I'll go now.

519
00:21:08,980 --> 00:21:10,710
You're even more eager than I am.

520
00:21:19,630 --> 00:21:22,050
[By the Canal]

521
00:21:27,550 --> 00:21:28,350
Master.

522
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:29,820
We're leaving.

523
00:21:30,630 --> 00:21:31,490
Everything's done?

524
00:21:32,180 --> 00:21:33,180
Alright, go home.

525
00:21:33,220 --> 00:21:33,590
Okay.

526
00:21:33,610 --> 00:21:35,030
Alright, we're leaving, Master.

527
00:21:35,070 --> 00:21:35,430
Go ahead.

528
00:21:35,470 --> 00:21:36,130
We're leaving.

529
00:21:36,190 --> 00:21:37,180
-Okay. 
-Bye.

530
00:21:38,110 --> 00:21:39,350
Goodbye, Master.

531
00:21:39,570 --> 00:21:40,530
Go home.

532
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:41,990
Don't play cards tonight.

533
00:21:42,100 --> 00:21:43,080
Okay.

534
00:21:56,140 --> 00:22:02,920
[Test Results of the Cerebrospinal Fluid Biomarker for Alzheimer's Disease]

535
00:22:03,590 --> 00:22:04,350
Everyone,

536
00:22:04,990 --> 00:22:07,540
I'll get straight to the point.

537
00:22:07,910 --> 00:22:09,210
Mr. Zhou

538
00:22:09,230 --> 00:22:12,270
was diagnosed with Alzheimer's disease a couple of days ago.

539
00:22:12,620 --> 00:22:14,370
I gathered everyone here today

540
00:22:14,590 --> 00:22:16,070
to inform you all about this

541
00:22:16,070 --> 00:22:17,620
so that you can be prepared.

542
00:22:17,660 --> 00:22:18,940
H-Has it been confirmed?

543
00:22:20,830 --> 00:22:21,930
This disease…

544
00:22:23,350 --> 00:22:24,720
is not easy to treat, is it?

545
00:22:25,780 --> 00:22:26,980
Well, people with this disease

546
00:22:27,540 --> 00:22:30,190
will gradually forget the people

547
00:22:30,230 --> 00:22:31,270
around them.

548
00:22:31,320 --> 00:22:32,390
In the most severe cases,

549
00:22:32,430 --> 00:22:34,470
they will even forget their families.

550
00:22:34,810 --> 00:22:37,340
So we all need to be mentally prepared.

551
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:38,280
You mean,

552
00:22:39,130 --> 00:22:40,160
he'll forget

553
00:22:40,190 --> 00:22:41,010
all of us?

554
00:22:41,030 --> 00:22:42,990
That's why we need to take this seriously.

555
00:22:43,010 --> 00:22:44,850
If Mr. Zhou has a memory lapse one day,

556
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:46,800
we all need to stay calm.

557
00:22:46,840 --> 00:22:48,220
We should play along

558
00:22:48,260 --> 00:22:50,010
and not let him sense anything unusual.

559
00:22:51,230 --> 00:22:53,880
But we don't know when he's normal

560
00:22:53,900 --> 00:22:56,070
and when he's having a memory lapse.

561
00:22:57,980 --> 00:23:00,660
I'll ask my friend working at the hospital about it.

562
00:23:00,830 --> 00:23:02,510
We should observe a patient

563
00:23:02,530 --> 00:23:05,430
to understand what this disease is really like.

564
00:23:05,550 --> 00:23:06,870
Then we'll know how to handle it.

565
00:23:06,890 --> 00:23:09,190
We need to know more about it, right?

566
00:23:09,210 --> 00:23:10,820
Now that Mr. Zhou is ill,

567
00:23:10,850 --> 00:23:13,490
can he still take care of his daily needs by himself?

568
00:23:13,510 --> 00:23:14,510
For now, he can.

569
00:23:14,550 --> 00:23:16,140
But we don't know about the future.

570
00:23:16,840 --> 00:23:17,600
Yeah.

571
00:23:17,680 --> 00:23:20,390
Then we need to get someone to watch him all day,

572
00:23:20,510 --> 00:23:21,880
don't we?

573
00:23:22,260 --> 00:23:23,520
We can't let him get lost.

574
00:23:23,550 --> 00:23:24,860
Watch him all day?

575
00:23:27,480 --> 00:23:28,990
Who can do that?

576
00:23:59,470 --> 00:24:00,990
How could this happen?

577
00:24:01,550 --> 00:24:03,070
W-We were just talking the other day

578
00:24:03,070 --> 00:24:04,070
about going to Italy together.

579
00:24:04,070 --> 00:24:05,670
I was just about to apply for a visa.

580
00:24:05,770 --> 00:24:07,420
Forget about Italy.

581
00:24:07,930 --> 00:24:10,050
It's too far. Forget about it.

582
00:24:12,070 --> 00:24:12,830
Chen Rui,

583
00:24:13,630 --> 00:24:14,630
I called you over

584
00:24:15,810 --> 00:24:17,310
to ask you for a favor.

585
00:24:17,340 --> 00:24:18,330
G-Go ahead.

586
00:24:18,360 --> 00:24:20,240
Just tell me what I can do to help.

587
00:24:22,060 --> 00:24:24,460
My dad doesn't know about his illness,

588
00:24:25,320 --> 00:24:26,750
and we don't want him to know.

589
00:24:27,430 --> 00:24:28,600
So,

590
00:24:29,270 --> 00:24:32,090
could you help me keep an eye on him?

591
00:24:32,130 --> 00:24:34,010
I'm worried he might get lost.

592
00:24:34,040 --> 00:24:36,710
No problem. We're together every day anyway.

593
00:24:36,740 --> 00:24:38,650
I'll keep an eye on him. Don't worry.

594
00:24:40,270 --> 00:24:41,510
Don't tell Haikuo

595
00:24:41,590 --> 00:24:42,360
about it.

596
00:24:43,670 --> 00:24:44,590
Why not?

597
00:24:45,710 --> 00:24:49,210
He's in Beijing and can't come back.

598
00:24:49,240 --> 00:24:50,390
It would just make him worry.

599
00:24:52,500 --> 00:24:53,300
That's true.

600
00:24:56,440 --> 00:24:57,360
Haikuo.

601
00:24:57,390 --> 00:24:58,200
Over here.

602
00:25:01,280 --> 00:25:02,400
What took you so long?

603
00:25:02,420 --> 00:25:03,260
I waited for you for ages.

604
00:25:03,290 --> 00:25:03,890
Mr. Zhou,

605
00:25:03,920 --> 00:25:04,680
pleasure to meet you.

606
00:25:04,700 --> 00:25:05,380
Welcome.

607
00:25:05,410 --> 00:25:05,780
Today,

608
00:25:05,800 --> 00:25:07,390
I'm going to show you three apartments.

609
00:25:07,430 --> 00:25:08,180
Take your time.

610
00:25:08,210 --> 00:25:08,730
You'll surely find a satisfying one.

611
00:25:08,770 --> 00:25:09,230
Let's go.

612
00:25:09,260 --> 00:25:09,870
Let's go.

613
00:25:11,950 --> 00:25:12,550
Mr. Zhou,

614
00:25:12,570 --> 00:25:13,570
please, this way.

615
00:25:13,610 --> 00:25:15,410
This is one of the best-selling new developments

616
00:25:15,430 --> 00:25:17,460
within the Fourth Ring Road.

617
00:25:17,500 --> 00:25:18,840
Take a look.

618
00:25:19,150 --> 00:25:20,580
This apartment is

619
00:25:20,630 --> 00:25:22,030
north-south facing with good ventilation.

620
00:25:22,030 --> 00:25:24,350
It has two bedrooms, two living rooms, and one bathroom.

621
00:25:24,380 --> 00:25:25,200
There's a lot of

622
00:25:25,220 --> 00:25:25,980
space.

623
00:25:26,020 --> 00:25:26,770
Look at this living room.

624
00:25:26,790 --> 00:25:28,120
It's 32 square meters in total.

625
00:25:28,150 --> 00:25:29,780
Mr. Zhou, take a look.

626
00:25:31,680 --> 00:25:32,550
Haikuo,

627
00:25:32,550 --> 00:25:33,110
come over.

628
00:25:33,110 --> 00:25:34,200
The view is great.

629
00:25:35,300 --> 00:25:36,310
Mr. Zhou?

630
00:25:37,990 --> 00:25:39,580
Are you not satisfied with this apartment?

631
00:25:39,610 --> 00:25:40,230
It's okay.

632
00:25:40,250 --> 00:25:40,770
I have other options for you.

633
00:25:40,830 --> 00:25:41,590
There's a 100-square-meter

634
00:25:41,590 --> 00:25:42,470
duplex.

635
00:25:42,470 --> 00:25:43,380
Let me show you.

636
00:25:44,860 --> 00:25:45,690
No need.

637
00:25:45,720 --> 00:25:46,620
Thank you.

638
00:25:46,650 --> 00:25:47,710
I'm busy today.

639
00:25:47,710 --> 00:25:48,630
Maybe next time.

640
00:25:48,800 --> 00:25:49,700
Let's go.

641
00:25:49,720 --> 00:25:50,460
Haikuo!

642
00:25:50,480 --> 00:25:51,370
Haikuo!

643
00:25:52,630 --> 00:25:53,610
Haikuo!

644
00:25:54,140 --> 00:25:55,920
Zhou Haikuo, what do you mean?

645
00:25:56,830 --> 00:25:58,160
I'm not planning to buy a house.

646
00:25:58,500 --> 00:25:59,390
Why not?

647
00:25:59,420 --> 00:26:01,200
I don't have money.

648
00:26:01,490 --> 00:26:02,550
Didn't Xie Wanghe say

649
00:26:02,550 --> 00:26:04,170
he would help you get stock options?

650
00:26:04,210 --> 00:26:06,300
I don't even know if the company will survive,

651
00:26:06,320 --> 00:26:07,550
so don't depend on the stock options.

652
00:26:07,580 --> 00:26:09,700
You think starting a business guarantees success?

653
00:26:09,710 --> 00:26:11,880
Then we can ask our parents for some money.

654
00:26:12,410 --> 00:26:13,630
I don't want to use my parents' money.

655
00:26:14,580 --> 00:26:15,880
Think about Mr. Du and Wenwen.

656
00:26:15,900 --> 00:26:16,990
Their parents paid the down payments for them,

657
00:26:16,990 --> 00:26:18,260
and then they'd pay off the mortgage themselves.

658
00:26:18,800 --> 00:26:19,890
In life,

659
00:26:20,310 --> 00:26:21,790
one should have a home of their own, right?

660
00:26:26,020 --> 00:26:27,980
Are you saying without a house, there's no home?

661
00:26:28,390 --> 00:26:30,350
I'm not asking for a big house.

662
00:26:30,660 --> 00:26:31,580
At least let me have

663
00:26:31,580 --> 00:26:32,920
a bedroom I can decorate myself.

664
00:26:32,920 --> 00:26:34,320
Even a small apartment would do.

665
00:26:34,350 --> 00:26:36,110
After we become rich…

666
00:26:36,110 --> 00:26:38,430
I'm very satisfied with the house I live in now.

667
00:26:39,110 --> 00:26:40,110
I don't want to change.

668
00:26:40,230 --> 00:26:40,820
Wait.

669
00:26:41,100 --> 00:26:42,940
Are you going to live in a rental house for the rest of your life?

670
00:26:42,960 --> 00:26:44,530
What's wrong with renting?

671
00:26:44,700 --> 00:26:46,360
Is life so unbearable in a rental house?

672
00:26:48,300 --> 00:26:49,110
Yes!

673
00:26:52,950 --> 00:26:54,380
Zhou Haikuo, if you leave now,

674
00:26:54,420 --> 00:26:56,390
don't ever come back to me!

675
00:26:58,890 --> 00:27:08,950
[Amour Bar]

676
00:26:59,560 --> 00:27:01,000
Enough.

677
00:27:01,020 --> 00:27:01,960
Stop drinking.

678
00:27:05,170 --> 00:27:06,880
Xiaohui isn't wrong.

679
00:27:07,250 --> 00:27:08,840
Having a house gives her peace of mind.

680
00:27:08,870 --> 00:27:10,080
My parents had a house.

681
00:27:10,470 --> 00:27:11,620
Did they have peace of mind?

682
00:27:11,770 --> 00:27:12,880
That's different.

683
00:27:13,020 --> 00:27:14,210
How is it different?

684
00:27:14,360 --> 00:27:15,390
In my opinion,

685
00:27:16,550 --> 00:27:17,600
a marriage certificate,

686
00:27:17,760 --> 00:27:18,510
a car,

687
00:27:18,510 --> 00:27:19,190
a house,

688
00:27:19,240 --> 00:27:20,120
and children—

689
00:27:20,370 --> 00:27:22,600
these things all seem to be the bonds of marriage

690
00:27:22,620 --> 00:27:24,590
that can make the relationship between two people stronger

691
00:27:24,630 --> 00:27:25,340
and more stable.

692
00:27:25,360 --> 00:27:27,800
But a truly unbreakable marriage

693
00:27:27,840 --> 00:27:29,490
doesn't need any of these things.

694
00:27:29,830 --> 00:27:32,000
Love alone is enough.

695
00:27:32,610 --> 00:27:35,300
Any relationship that needs external things to maintain

696
00:27:35,320 --> 00:27:37,590
is fragile

697
00:27:37,810 --> 00:27:39,340
and will fail sooner or later.

698
00:27:39,370 --> 00:27:41,050
My parents are a prime example.

699
00:27:41,070 --> 00:27:42,040
In my opinion,

700
00:27:42,120 --> 00:27:43,940
you just don't love Xiaohui enough.

701
00:27:44,100 --> 00:27:45,620
If you really loved Xiaohui,

702
00:27:45,710 --> 00:27:46,310
you'd not just give her a house

703
00:27:46,310 --> 00:27:47,210
but also your life.

704
00:27:47,310 --> 00:27:48,980
Shut up!

705
00:27:49,550 --> 00:27:50,830
Let me put it this way.

706
00:27:51,050 --> 00:27:52,640
If Xiaohui got sick

707
00:27:52,710 --> 00:27:53,990
and needed a kidney, would you give her yours?

708
00:27:53,990 --> 00:27:54,710
Of course.

709
00:27:54,750 --> 00:27:55,470
That's it.

710
00:27:55,550 --> 00:27:56,300
You'd give her a kidney

711
00:27:56,300 --> 00:27:56,950
but not a house?

712
00:27:56,990 --> 00:27:58,330
Are you crazy?

713
00:28:00,300 --> 00:28:02,440
You're the one who's crazy.

714
00:28:03,800 --> 00:28:05,420
I can understand that.

715
00:28:06,340 --> 00:28:07,190
Giving her his kidney

716
00:28:07,900 --> 00:28:09,670
means Haikuo loves her.

717
00:28:09,690 --> 00:28:11,300
It shows he cares for her.

718
00:28:11,630 --> 00:28:12,900
But being forced

719
00:28:13,460 --> 00:28:14,980
to buy her a house

720
00:28:15,020 --> 00:28:17,360
makes you feel like she doesn't trust you.

721
00:28:17,910 --> 00:28:19,230
It almost feels like

722
00:28:19,260 --> 00:28:20,110
she doesn't love you.

723
00:28:20,960 --> 00:28:21,910
That's it!

724
00:28:23,740 --> 00:28:24,410
I love her.

725
00:28:24,430 --> 00:28:26,130
I want to give her

726
00:28:26,150 --> 00:28:27,140
a better life,

727
00:28:27,170 --> 00:28:29,250
and I'll work hard for that.

728
00:28:29,470 --> 00:28:31,080
But she can't force me!

729
00:28:31,090 --> 00:28:32,470
It makes me feel that

730
00:28:32,660 --> 00:28:33,810
our relationship

731
00:28:33,870 --> 00:28:36,090
is bought with this house

732
00:28:36,120 --> 00:28:37,410
and it's fragile.

733
00:28:37,430 --> 00:28:38,120
Understand?

734
00:28:38,150 --> 00:28:38,850
Fine.

735
00:28:39,740 --> 00:28:40,830
If you really break up with her,

736
00:28:40,860 --> 00:28:42,000
don't come crying to us.

737
00:28:43,450 --> 00:28:44,410
I'll change the locks.

738
00:28:44,440 --> 00:28:45,890
Go cry to Xiaohui.

739
00:28:47,550 --> 00:28:48,390
Alright.

740
00:28:48,420 --> 00:28:49,280
You two drink.

741
00:28:49,300 --> 00:28:50,160
I'm leaving.

742
00:28:52,770 --> 00:28:53,840
I'm leaving!

743
00:28:56,700 --> 00:28:57,500
Go ahead.

744
00:28:57,780 --> 00:28:58,740
I'll talk to the river.

745
00:28:59,520 --> 00:29:00,590
I'm really leaving!

746
00:29:00,590 --> 00:29:01,150
Take care.

747
00:29:01,150 --> 00:29:01,870
Go ahead and jump.

748
00:29:01,870 --> 00:29:02,880
You're not stopping me?

749
00:29:02,880 --> 00:29:03,960
Jump.

750
00:29:07,970 --> 00:29:08,990
What are you going to do?

751
00:29:09,010 --> 00:29:09,840
Dance!

752
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:25,480
Come here!

753
00:29:25,510 --> 00:29:26,610
Come here!

754
00:29:27,110 --> 00:29:27,890
Hurry up!

755
00:29:41,150 --> 00:29:41,990
Not bad.

756
00:29:43,310 --> 00:29:44,180
Your response

757
00:29:44,310 --> 00:29:45,590
is faster than I expected.

758
00:29:45,880 --> 00:29:48,070
You're young and full of energy.

759
00:29:49,040 --> 00:29:51,200
Yuntuan will catch up soon.

760
00:29:51,510 --> 00:29:52,880
Then surpass them again.

761
00:29:52,980 --> 00:29:55,060
Competition is all about spirit.

762
00:29:56,680 --> 00:29:58,530
We need more people.

763
00:29:58,790 --> 00:30:00,910
Yuntuan's HR department alone

764
00:30:00,990 --> 00:30:02,470
takes up half a floor.

765
00:30:02,950 --> 00:30:04,280
I know it's been hard for you.

766
00:30:04,470 --> 00:30:05,100
Hang in there.

767
00:30:05,380 --> 00:30:06,870
I've already started reaching out for Series D funding.

768
00:30:07,030 --> 00:30:07,860
Which company?

769
00:30:08,150 --> 00:30:09,380
I can't tell you for now.

770
00:30:09,910 --> 00:30:11,200
I'll let you know when it's done.

771
00:30:17,230 --> 00:30:17,990
Mr. Meng.

772
00:30:19,800 --> 00:30:20,820
Well…

773
00:30:21,780 --> 00:30:22,540
What's it?

774
00:30:24,350 --> 00:30:25,910
If we get the funding,

775
00:30:26,040 --> 00:30:27,380
before Series E,

776
00:30:27,630 --> 00:30:29,340
can you give my two friends

777
00:30:29,370 --> 00:30:30,580
some stock options?

778
00:30:31,590 --> 00:30:32,590
The amount doesn't matter.

779
00:30:32,590 --> 00:30:34,140
The gesture itself matters.

780
00:30:34,470 --> 00:30:36,350
I hope Bee can make them

781
00:30:36,400 --> 00:30:37,980
feel included.

782
00:30:43,470 --> 00:30:47,400
So without stock options, they don't feel included?

783
00:30:47,400 --> 00:30:48,590
Not exactly...

784
00:30:48,590 --> 00:30:50,350
In the whole company,

785
00:30:50,480 --> 00:30:51,750
how many people have stock options?

786
00:30:57,960 --> 00:30:59,590
I can share mine with them.

787
00:31:00,210 --> 00:31:01,550
Just don't tell them.

788
00:31:05,780 --> 00:31:06,810
You're close friends.

789
00:31:07,790 --> 00:31:09,310
After you succeed,

790
00:31:09,340 --> 00:31:11,120
buy them a nice car.

791
00:31:11,350 --> 00:31:12,110
That'll be enough.

792
00:31:12,880 --> 00:31:14,400
I'm not teaching you to be stingy.

793
00:31:16,100 --> 00:31:17,230
It's just that

794
00:31:17,400 --> 00:31:18,820
people are unpredictable.

795
00:31:19,180 --> 00:31:20,830
Great kindness can lead to resentment.

796
00:31:21,920 --> 00:31:22,860
Look at me.

797
00:31:23,470 --> 00:31:25,070
I started my business in college.

798
00:31:25,950 --> 00:31:27,850
And today, none of my old friends

799
00:31:29,280 --> 00:31:30,120
are still around.

800
00:31:30,360 --> 00:31:32,420
It's a hard-learned lesson.

801
00:31:33,110 --> 00:31:34,240
We're different.

802
00:31:34,570 --> 00:31:35,590
We're childhood friends.

803
00:31:35,670 --> 00:31:36,710
We were neighbors.

804
00:31:36,730 --> 00:31:37,910
So what?

805
00:31:38,570 --> 00:31:39,560
Even blood brothers

806
00:31:39,860 --> 00:31:41,000
fight tooth and nail

807
00:31:41,020 --> 00:31:43,050
over a bit of inheritance.

808
00:31:43,580 --> 00:31:44,230
And think about

809
00:31:44,230 --> 00:31:46,070
those successful big companies.

810
00:31:46,950 --> 00:31:48,070
How many can you name

811
00:31:48,100 --> 00:31:49,910
that are still owned by their founding members?

812
00:31:50,520 --> 00:31:51,490
Naive.

813
00:32:08,010 --> 00:32:08,680
Son.

814
00:32:10,100 --> 00:32:10,630
Mom?

815
00:32:10,630 --> 00:32:11,350
Get in.

816
00:32:19,970 --> 00:32:21,290
What are you doing here?

817
00:32:21,490 --> 00:32:22,550
Let's go have dinner.

818
00:32:40,430 --> 00:32:41,830
The head chef of this restaurant

819
00:32:41,850 --> 00:32:43,210
was your father's apprentice.

820
00:32:43,230 --> 00:32:45,020
The restaurant's owner poached him with a high salary.

821
00:32:45,150 --> 00:32:47,230
Try it and see if it tastes the same.

822
00:32:48,820 --> 00:32:49,530
Not bad.

823
00:32:50,780 --> 00:32:52,190
I'll give you a card later.

824
00:32:52,220 --> 00:32:53,840
Bring Wanghe and the others here to eat.

825
00:32:55,470 --> 00:32:57,010
How's your dad doing lately?

826
00:32:59,270 --> 00:33:01,100
Don't you two call each other?

827
00:33:03,110 --> 00:33:04,280
We haven't been in touch for a long time.

828
00:33:04,300 --> 00:33:05,500
We're both busy.

829
00:33:08,130 --> 00:33:10,820
I occasionally call your grandpa to check on things,

830
00:33:10,930 --> 00:33:12,920
but he only shares good news with me.

831
00:33:12,970 --> 00:33:14,700
Because there's no bad news.

832
00:33:15,830 --> 00:33:16,830
You're the same.

833
00:33:16,850 --> 00:33:19,270
Every time I ask, you say everything's fine.

834
00:33:19,290 --> 00:33:20,460
You won't tell me anything.

835
00:33:21,080 --> 00:33:22,830
It's true that everything's fine,

836
00:33:22,870 --> 00:33:24,350
or I would definitely tell you.

837
00:33:25,820 --> 00:33:27,130
What about you and Xiaohui?

838
00:33:30,360 --> 00:33:31,930
Why did you two fight if everything was fine?

839
00:33:38,390 --> 00:33:39,460
She went to you?

840
00:33:39,590 --> 00:33:40,390
Yes.

841
00:33:40,480 --> 00:33:41,550
She kept crying.

842
00:33:42,340 --> 00:33:43,370
It's your fault.

843
00:33:44,290 --> 00:33:46,720
Why make such a fuss over a house?

844
00:33:46,750 --> 00:33:47,770
As a girl,

845
00:33:47,800 --> 00:33:50,160
she needs to feel secure.

846
00:33:50,390 --> 00:33:52,260
You hurt her feelings.

847
00:33:52,680 --> 00:33:54,150
Can a house

848
00:33:55,590 --> 00:33:57,190
really make her feel secure?

849
00:33:57,220 --> 00:33:58,050
Of course.

850
00:33:58,080 --> 00:34:00,250
Having a house means having a home.

851
00:34:01,660 --> 00:34:05,060
But you and Dad had a house and a home.

852
00:34:08,690 --> 00:34:09,960
At your age,

853
00:34:09,960 --> 00:34:11,429
you should be past your rebellious phase.

854
00:34:11,449 --> 00:34:13,219
This is your problem.

855
00:34:13,639 --> 00:34:15,159
Don't bring up your dad and me.

856
00:34:16,710 --> 00:34:18,440
We had a house.

857
00:34:18,870 --> 00:34:20,480
Life was not bad.

858
00:34:20,750 --> 00:34:22,670
My dad is down-to-earth.

859
00:34:24,290 --> 00:34:26,409
I believe you didn't feel insecure.

860
00:34:26,440 --> 00:34:27,070
No.

861
00:34:27,090 --> 00:34:27,780
I didn't feel insecure.

862
00:34:29,949 --> 00:34:31,330
But you still left.

863
00:34:33,690 --> 00:34:35,590
So, a sense of security

864
00:34:35,630 --> 00:34:37,219
is not important for marriage,

865
00:34:38,100 --> 00:34:39,370
and it's not a necessity.

866
00:34:40,630 --> 00:34:41,810
You felt secure,

867
00:34:42,590 --> 00:34:45,389
yet you still found the mundane life boring.

868
00:34:45,409 --> 00:34:46,590
So why should I pursue

869
00:34:46,590 --> 00:34:47,699
the so-called sense of security?

870
00:34:56,580 --> 00:34:57,990
Sorry, Son.

871
00:34:58,020 --> 00:34:59,720
What happened between your dad and me

872
00:35:00,110 --> 00:35:02,890
traumatized you.

873
00:35:04,180 --> 00:35:05,750
That's not what I mean.

874
00:35:09,650 --> 00:35:11,100
When you were young,

875
00:35:11,320 --> 00:35:13,040
there were things you wouldn't understand even if I told you.

876
00:35:13,220 --> 00:35:14,690
Now that you've grown up,

877
00:35:14,700 --> 00:35:15,910
I can tell you about them.

878
00:35:17,630 --> 00:35:20,700
I've only loved one man in my entire life.

879
00:35:20,810 --> 00:35:22,080
That's your dad.

880
00:35:22,470 --> 00:35:23,650
I still love him.

881
00:35:26,240 --> 00:35:27,200
But

882
00:35:27,940 --> 00:35:29,830
the life he gave me…

883
00:35:30,680 --> 00:35:33,400
made me feel depressed and suffocated.

884
00:35:33,830 --> 00:35:37,060
I'd rather face all kinds of hardships outside

885
00:35:37,110 --> 00:35:40,570
than go back to that unchanging life

886
00:35:40,970 --> 00:35:42,730
where I could see how it would end.

887
00:35:46,750 --> 00:35:47,560
So,

888
00:35:48,700 --> 00:35:51,240
your dad and I parted on good terms.

889
00:35:51,910 --> 00:35:53,690
We both have resentment in our hearts,

890
00:35:54,460 --> 00:35:55,550
but we also wish each other well.

891
00:35:57,820 --> 00:36:01,160
Are you sure Dad wishes you well?

892
00:36:01,220 --> 00:36:02,420
Of course!

893
00:36:02,440 --> 00:36:03,750
He loves me very much too.

894
00:36:03,770 --> 00:36:05,950
That's why he let me go.

895
00:36:10,810 --> 00:36:12,030
As for you and Xiaohui,

896
00:36:12,050 --> 00:36:13,920
I don't care about what will happen in the future.

897
00:36:13,950 --> 00:36:15,730
If you truly love her,

898
00:36:15,780 --> 00:36:18,240
I hope you think through a few things.

899
00:36:19,490 --> 00:36:20,220
First,

900
00:36:20,240 --> 00:36:22,710
can you give her the life she wants?

901
00:36:23,170 --> 00:36:23,990
Second,

902
00:36:24,230 --> 00:36:25,700
will that kind of life

903
00:36:26,180 --> 00:36:28,060
make you miserable?

904
00:36:29,000 --> 00:36:30,500
Third and most importantly,

905
00:36:31,300 --> 00:36:32,310
after breaking up with her,

906
00:36:33,030 --> 00:36:35,030
will you regret it?

907
00:36:40,060 --> 00:36:40,740
How about you?

908
00:36:41,240 --> 00:36:41,950
Do you regret it?

909
00:36:46,990 --> 00:36:49,740
I know what my answer is.

910
00:36:50,450 --> 00:36:52,710
You need to figure out what your answer is.

911
00:36:53,020 --> 00:36:56,000
Everyone is responsible for their own life.

912
00:36:56,500 --> 00:36:59,850
Neither your dad nor I have the right to make choices for you.

913
00:37:20,660 --> 00:37:21,900
♫Inexplicable and strange♫

914
00:37:22,860 --> 00:37:25,730
♫I can't both love you and let you go♫

915
00:37:26,840 --> 00:37:28,230
♫I want to say something but keep silent♫

916
00:37:29,110 --> 00:37:32,410
♫Just quietly listening to my heart thudding♫

917
00:37:34,280 --> 00:37:35,950
♫But you don't know♫

918
00:37:36,450 --> 00:37:40,850
♫When I turned away, my eyes were wet too♫

919
00:37:41,450 --> 00:37:43,190
♫I was already giving my all♫

920
00:37:43,910 --> 00:37:47,630
♫To maintain a final bit of dignity♫

921
00:37:48,370 --> 00:37:49,160
♫Fortunately♫

922
00:37:49,690 --> 00:37:51,610
♫You once gave me a warm hug♫

923
00:37:51,830 --> 00:37:52,950
Tonight…

924
00:37:52,460 --> 00:37:53,000
♫Unfortunately♫

925
00:37:53,460 --> 00:37:55,390
♫I can't have you, yet I still crave you♫

926
00:37:53,990 --> 00:37:55,230
my mom and I

927
00:37:55,870 --> 00:37:56,600
♫How can I decide♫

928
00:37:55,950 --> 00:37:57,100
ate this.

929
00:37:57,240 --> 00:37:59,400
♫Which is messier, the beginning or the end?♫

930
00:38:00,300 --> 00:38:02,290
♫Both are unforgettable♫

931
00:38:02,780 --> 00:38:04,470
♫Why does your kindness vanish♫

932
00:38:05,050 --> 00:38:06,630
♫The moment I let go?♫

933
00:38:07,360 --> 00:38:08,670
♫How could you leave me so heartbroken♫

934
00:38:07,540 --> 00:38:08,300
Sorry.

935
00:38:09,270 --> 00:38:10,940
♫That even my tears feel like they're burning?♫

936
00:38:10,320 --> 00:38:11,300
All right.

937
00:38:11,730 --> 00:38:12,800
I won't leave.

938
00:38:11,870 --> 00:38:14,600
♫Maybe it's a relief that we're not meant for each other♫

939
00:38:13,220 --> 00:38:13,920
Don't worry.

940
00:38:15,260 --> 00:38:17,310
♫No need to suffer too long♫

941
00:38:16,990 --> 00:38:17,910
Stop crying.

942
00:38:17,750 --> 00:38:19,160
♫Why can you forget my kindness♫

943
00:38:19,680 --> 00:38:21,520
♫The moment you let go?♫

944
00:38:21,890 --> 00:38:22,980
♫Making me look like a fool♫

945
00:38:23,540 --> 00:38:25,740
♫Even my longing feels like begging♫

946
00:38:26,450 --> 00:38:27,910
♫I'll let go eventually♫

947
00:38:28,320 --> 00:38:32,270
♫I'll say goodbye and disturb you no more♫

948
00:38:36,550 --> 00:38:37,680
I wonder

949
00:38:37,970 --> 00:38:39,710
if he'll break up with Xiaohui.

950
00:38:40,460 --> 00:38:41,460
It won't come to that.

951
00:38:42,670 --> 00:38:43,550
How do you know?

952
00:38:43,580 --> 00:38:45,430
Xiaohui loves him so much.

953
00:38:45,540 --> 00:38:47,320
He didn't reply to her messages for a few days,

954
00:38:47,390 --> 00:38:48,920
and her eyes were swollen from crying.

955
00:38:49,030 --> 00:38:51,050
She dragged me to meet Haikuo's mom with her.

956
00:38:51,270 --> 00:38:52,310
She was so humble.

957
00:38:56,650 --> 00:38:58,270
If you were her,

958
00:38:58,690 --> 00:38:59,690
what would you do?

959
00:38:59,710 --> 00:39:01,110
You mean the house?

960
00:39:02,380 --> 00:39:03,840
What kind of house do you want?

961
00:39:06,070 --> 00:39:07,110
I don't want

962
00:39:07,470 --> 00:39:08,320
a house

963
00:39:08,470 --> 00:39:09,580
but an RV.

964
00:39:10,070 --> 00:39:12,630
The kind you can drive around everywhere.

965
00:39:12,990 --> 00:39:14,140
When I've earned enough money,

966
00:39:14,280 --> 00:39:15,420
I'll drive my RV

967
00:39:15,470 --> 00:39:17,030
to travel all over the world.

968
00:39:17,750 --> 00:39:18,770
Wherever I go,

969
00:39:18,950 --> 00:39:19,810
I'll set up a tent,

970
00:39:19,950 --> 00:39:20,830
build a fire,

971
00:39:20,990 --> 00:39:21,830
grill some skewers,

972
00:39:21,850 --> 00:39:22,760
and open a beer.

973
00:39:22,990 --> 00:39:23,690
Perfect.

974
00:39:25,030 --> 00:39:25,940
Where do you want to go the most?

975
00:39:26,070 --> 00:39:27,280
The place doesn't matter.

976
00:39:27,650 --> 00:39:29,830
What matters is who I travel with.

977
00:39:33,230 --> 00:39:33,830
Yes.

978
00:39:37,230 --> 00:39:38,040
What about you?

979
00:39:38,870 --> 00:39:40,070
If the company goes public

980
00:39:40,110 --> 00:39:41,410
and you achieve financial freedom,

981
00:39:41,480 --> 00:39:43,020
how do you plan to live your life?

982
00:39:44,590 --> 00:39:47,430
Travel with the girl I love.

983
00:39:50,120 --> 00:39:51,830
That's my dream.

984
00:39:51,870 --> 00:39:53,100
What about your own dream?

985
00:39:53,130 --> 00:39:54,920
Dreams can overlap, you know.

986
00:39:55,510 --> 00:39:56,990
If I were to travel,

987
00:39:57,350 --> 00:39:58,690
I'd sail a ship

988
00:39:58,710 --> 00:40:00,380
along the canal to leave the country,

989
00:40:00,730 --> 00:40:03,220
cruising along the coastline.

990
00:40:04,830 --> 00:40:06,300
Greece is by the sea, right?

991
00:40:06,670 --> 00:40:07,470
Yes.

992
00:40:08,660 --> 00:40:11,420
Then I'll take wedding photos by the Aegean Sea.

993
00:40:11,550 --> 00:40:12,870
They must look great.

994
00:40:12,960 --> 00:40:14,020
Wedding photos?

995
00:40:15,710 --> 00:40:16,730
With whom?

996
00:40:18,660 --> 00:40:20,010
Certainly not with you.

997
00:40:22,710 --> 00:40:23,950
You don't know that.

998
00:40:26,660 --> 00:40:27,830
I said the shrimp is good.

999
00:40:28,790 --> 00:40:29,840
Trust me.

1000
00:40:29,870 --> 00:40:30,940
This restaurant is great.

1001
00:40:31,010 --> 00:40:32,100
Welcome.

1002
00:40:32,270 --> 00:40:33,510
Let's drink tonight.

1003
00:40:36,070 --> 00:40:36,670
Go in.

1004
00:40:36,710 --> 00:40:37,190
Wait, wait.

1005
00:40:37,190 --> 00:40:37,950
Sorry.

1006
00:40:38,190 --> 00:40:39,860
I-I made a mistake.

1007
00:40:40,030 --> 00:40:41,070
It's not this restaurant.

1008
00:40:41,180 --> 00:40:43,100
The shrimps here are very small.

1009
00:40:43,400 --> 00:40:44,740
Let me take you somewhere else.

1010
00:40:50,750 --> 00:40:51,560
Bye.

1011
00:40:54,310 --> 00:40:54,870
Fenghua.

1012
00:40:55,700 --> 00:40:57,070
Are you still using that plaster?

1013
00:40:58,060 --> 00:40:59,220
Yes.

1014
00:40:59,500 --> 00:41:00,730
My lower back hasn't been hurting much lately.

1015
00:41:01,660 --> 00:41:03,400
Avoid heavy lifting.

1016
00:41:03,870 --> 00:41:04,500
Don't stay up late.

1017
00:41:04,530 --> 00:41:05,650
Eat meals on time.

1018
00:41:06,100 --> 00:41:07,130
Brush your teeth with warm water.

1019
00:41:07,170 --> 00:41:08,780
The foot bath water should be hot. You hear me?

1020
00:41:09,470 --> 00:41:11,700
I got it. You nag even more than my mom.

1021
00:41:12,070 --> 00:41:12,870
Bye.

1022
00:41:14,150 --> 00:41:14,680
Well,

1023
00:41:14,710 --> 00:41:15,900
wait for me a moment.

1024
00:41:26,230 --> 00:41:26,990
Here, this is for you.

1025
00:41:27,030 --> 00:41:27,750
What is it?

1026
00:41:28,070 --> 00:41:29,550
Read it, and you'll know.

1027
00:41:29,320 --> 00:41:31,950
[Guide for Reducing Costs and Increasing Efficiency of Delivery Riders in Haidian District, Beijing]

1028
00:41:30,740 --> 00:41:34,380
"Guide for Reducing Costs and Increasing Efficiency of Delivery Riders in Haidian District."

1029
00:41:32,050 --> 00:41:34,190
[Per Capita Consumption Range in Haidian District, Beijing]

1030
00:41:41,190 --> 00:41:42,070
Xia Fenghua,

1031
00:41:44,410 --> 00:41:46,610
I sincerely invite you again

1032
00:41:47,010 --> 00:41:48,220
to join Bee.

1033
00:41:50,870 --> 00:41:52,240
Not interested.

1034
00:41:52,390 --> 00:41:53,560
Why not?

1035
00:41:53,590 --> 00:41:55,460
When I took over this station,

1036
00:41:56,070 --> 00:41:57,390
it was almost going under.

1037
00:41:58,850 --> 00:42:01,240
At that time, we were all at a loss,

1038
00:42:01,520 --> 00:42:03,030
not knowing what the future held.

1039
00:42:03,810 --> 00:42:05,850
People were leaving every day.

1040
00:42:05,870 --> 00:42:08,700
At the toughest time, only four people were left.

1041
00:42:08,900 --> 00:42:10,430
We didn't know where the next meal would come from.

1042
00:42:11,540 --> 00:42:12,990
I was really scared.

1043
00:42:13,440 --> 00:42:15,900
So I secretly set a goal for myself:

1044
00:42:15,980 --> 00:42:17,030
within three years,

1045
00:42:17,050 --> 00:42:19,020
I would not only keep this station running

1046
00:42:19,140 --> 00:42:21,470
but also make sure everyone earned money,

1047
00:42:21,490 --> 00:42:24,480
and I'd be the station chief of the year.

1048
00:42:24,680 --> 00:42:26,960
That goal hasn't been achieved yet.

1049
00:42:27,500 --> 00:42:28,880
I can't give up now.

1050
00:42:29,130 --> 00:42:30,200
Compared to them,

1051
00:42:31,520 --> 00:42:32,920
I need you more.

1052
00:42:34,500 --> 00:42:35,430
Wanghe,

1053
00:42:36,260 --> 00:42:37,850
I know you care about me

1054
00:42:38,310 --> 00:42:39,150
and don't want me to push myself too hard.

1055
00:42:40,270 --> 00:42:41,390
But it's okay.

1056
00:42:41,420 --> 00:42:42,660
I'm quite happy.

1057
00:42:43,540 --> 00:42:44,620
Being needed

1058
00:42:44,650 --> 00:42:46,240
makes me feel powerful.

1059
00:42:47,870 --> 00:42:49,510
All these years in Beijing,

1060
00:42:50,180 --> 00:42:51,620
I've been like a wild grass,

1061
00:42:51,640 --> 00:42:52,870
struggling to survive.

1062
00:42:54,180 --> 00:42:55,520
Making it to today,

1063
00:42:55,990 --> 00:42:57,110
I feel like

1064
00:42:57,550 --> 00:42:58,950
I'm finally about to bloom.

